# Docker dev stack

Project name: `laravel-ecommerce` (`name:` in `docker-compose.yml`).

## Services

| Service    | Image / build                        | Role                              |
|------------|--------------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| `postgres`  | `postgres:16-alpine`                | Database (PostgreSQL 16)          |
| `app`       | `docker/php/Dockerfile` → `development` | PHP 8.2-FPM, runs Laravel         |
| `nginx`     | `nginx:1.27-alpine`                 | Reverse proxy → `app:9000`        |
| `node`      | `node:22-bookworm-slim`             | Vite HMR dev server               |
| `queue`     | same build as `app`                 | `php artisan queue:work`          |

## URLs (dev)

- App: **http://localhost:8080** (`HTTP_PORT` env, default `8080`)
- Vite HMR: **http://localhost:5173** (`VITE_PORT`, default `5173`)

## First-time setup

```bash
docker compose run --rm app composer install
docker compose up -d
docker compose exec app php artisan migrate --seed
```

## Day-to-day commands

```bash
# Start / stop
docker compose up -d
docker compose down

# Artisan (always exec into app, not locally)
docker compose exec app php artisan migrate
docker compose exec app php artisan migrate:fresh --seed
docker compose exec app php artisan test
docker compose exec app php artisan routes:smoke

# npm (exec into node service)
docker compose exec node npm run build
docker compose exec node npm ci

# Logs
docker compose logs -f app
docker compose logs -f queue
```

## Key rules

- **Never run `php artisan` or `composer` locally** when the stack is up — always `docker compose exec app`.
- **Never run commands that affect other Docker projects** on this machine.
- Code is bind-mounted at `/var/www/html`; `vendor` and `node_modules` live in named volumes (`vendor_data`, `node_modules_data`) — do not delete them carelessly.
- DB credentials default: host `postgres`, db/user/pass `laravel`/`postgres`/`postgres` (override via `.env`).
- `WAIT_FOR_DB=1` in `app` and `queue` means they wait for Postgres health before starting php-fpm.
- Production image: `docker-compose.prod.yml` + `docker/nginx/Dockerfile.prod`. Never use prod compose for local dev.
